<!-- ══════ FAQ ══════ -->
<section class="faq-section">
  <div class="eyebrow"><span class="eyebrow-line"></span><span class="eyebrow-text">Common Questions</span></div>
  <h2 class="section-title">FREQUENTLY<br>ASKED<br>QUESTIONS.</h2>
  <div class="gold-rule"></div>
  <div class="faq-list">
    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-q">How much does carpet installation cost in Halifax?<span class="faq-icon">+</span></button>
      <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">Carpet pricing depends on the area to be covered, carpet grade and pile, and whether stairs are included. We provide free quotes — basic installs are very affordable, and we can show you options across a range of price points.</div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-q">Do you supply the carpet or do I provide it?<span class="faq-icon">+</span></button>
      <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">Either works. We can source carpet through our suppliers, or you can purchase carpet yourself and we'll install it. If you supply your own, just let us know the product so we can ensure we have the right tools and adhesives.</div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-q">How long does carpet installation take?<span class="faq-icon">+</span></button>
      <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">A single room typically takes half a day to a full day. A full-home carpet install usually takes one to two days. Stair carpet is typically completed in a day as well. We'll confirm the timeline in your quote.</div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-q">Can you install carpet on stairs?<span class="faq-icon">+</span></button>
      <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">Yes — carpet stairs are one of our specialties. We do waterfall installs, pattern-matched cuts, and cap-and-band finishes. Tight corners, clean lines, no wrinkles — done properly the first time.</div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-q">Do you remove the old carpet before installing?<span class="faq-icon">+</span></button>
      <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">Yes — old carpet and tack strips are removed and disposed of as part of the job. We prep the subfloor before laying the new carpet and pad so you get a clean, professional finish.</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

